Herbivore suppression potential of the full coccinellid community varied between habitats (Kruskal-Wallis, H2=1610.6, p<0.01, 
      
       Table 3
      ). Herbivore suppression potential was highest in annual crops, and lowest in forests.

No significant trend was observed in the modeled herbivore suppression potential of the coccinellid community over time in any of the habitat groups (
      
       Figure 4A
      ). Herbivore suppression potential due to native species exhibited a significant linear decrease over time in annual and perennial crop habitats (annual: slope=-0.0030 ±0.0007, p<0.01; perennial: slope=-0.0074± 0.0005, p<0.01) but no trend was observed in forest habitats (
      
       Figure 4B
      ).

